248
00:16:04,840 --> 00:16:07,480
Like Elle MacPherson[br]or the girl at the Xerox place?

249
00:16:07,720 --> 00:16:10,280
-With the bellybutton ring?[br]-I know.

250
00:16:10,680 --> 00:16:13,480
And then all of a sudden,[br]your mom pops into your head.

251
00:16:14,680 --> 00:16:17,520
And you' re, like,[br]"Mom, get out of here! "

252
00:16:18,440 --> 00:16:20,910
But after that,[br]you can't think of anything else.

253
00:16:21,160 --> 00:16:25,760
And you can't stop what you' re doing.[br]So it's kind of like you' re. . .

254
00:16:26,560 --> 00:16:27,520
. . .you know. . .

255
00:16:27,760 --> 00:16:28,800
. . .you know. . . .

256
00:16:29,240 --> 00:16:30,310
You don't know!

257
00:16:32,440 --> 00:16:33,480
Your mom?

258
00:16:34,440 --> 00:16:37,750
You' re telling me about your mom?[br]What's the matter with you?

259
00:16:38,680 --> 00:16:41,520
-You said--[br]-I said "share," not "scare" !

260
00:16:41,800 --> 00:16:43,400
Go sit over there!

261
00:16:48,880 --> 00:16:50,110
We' re back!

262
00:16:52,280 --> 00:16:54,000
What are you guys doing together?

263
00:16:54,240 --> 00:16:57,630
Joey and Janice's Day of Fun!

264
00:16:59,800 --> 00:17:01,030
Really?

265
00:17:01,280 --> 00:17:03,510
We went to a Mets game.[br]We got Chinese food.

266
00:17:03,760 --> 00:17:06,800
And, you know, I love this woman.

267
00:17:08,160 --> 00:17:10,390
You have got competition, buddy.

268
00:17:10,840 --> 00:17:14,520
Well, I just came by[br]to give you a kiss.

269
00:17:15,840 --> 00:17:20,600
I have to go pick up the baby.[br]So, I'll see you later, sweetheart.

270
00:17:20,880 --> 00:17:22,030
You too, Chandler.

271
00:17:30,560 --> 00:17:34,880
-You still can't stand her, can you?[br]-I' m sorry, I tried! I really did!

272
00:17:37,640 --> 00:17:39,520
I appreciate you giving it a shot.

273
00:17:40,000 --> 00:17:41,840
But you know, the good thing. . .

274
00:17:42,080 --> 00:17:45,390
. . .is that we spent the whole day[br]together and I survived.

275
00:17:45,640 --> 00:17:48,600
And what's even more amazing,[br]so did she.

276
00:17:48,880 --> 00:17:50,720
It was Bat Day at Shea Stadium.

277
00:17:52,880 --> 00:17:54,000
I guess that's something.

278
00:17:54,200 --> 00:17:55,920
Oh, man, that's huge!

279
00:17:56,160 --> 00:17:59,240
Now I know I can stand to be[br]around her. Which means. . .

280
00:17:59,480 --> 00:18:01,120
. . .I get to hang out with you.

281
00:18:01,360 --> 00:18:04,000
Which is kind of[br]the whole point anyway.

282
00:18:08,680 --> 00:18:13,000
Oh, hey! We stopped by[br]the coffee shop and ran into Ross.

283
00:18:17,480 --> 00:18:19,080
Oh, God.

284
00:18:19,760 --> 00:18:22,200
If it makes you feel any better,[br]I do it too.

285
00:18:25,040 --> 00:18:26,800
-Really?[br]-Oh, yeah!

286
00:18:27,040 --> 00:18:30,000
I always picture your mom[br]when I' m having sex.

287
00:18:34,280 --> 00:18:36,560
April 12, 1861.

288
00:18:40,480 --> 00:18:43,680
The United States garrison[br]at Fort Sumter was fired upon.

289
00:18:44,400 --> 00:18:46,550
It is now under bombardment by--

290
00:18:57,400 --> 00:18:58,880
Dad! What are you doing?

291
00:18:59,120 --> 00:19:03,560
It's your mother's bridge night, so I[br]came into the city for a Moni-cuddle.

292
00:19:07,040 --> 00:19:09,430
Since when did you start[br]smoking cigars?

293
00:19:10,440 --> 00:19:13,640
I don't.[br]I just like the smell of them.

294
00:19:14,680 --> 00:19:17,600
So what are you really doing here?

295
00:19:17,840 --> 00:19:19,840
I just wanted to make sure[br]you' re okay.

296
00:19:21,480 --> 00:19:23,080
Why wouldn't I be okay?

297
00:19:23,320 --> 00:19:24,640
I saw Richard.

298
00:19:27,800 --> 00:19:29,400
So how you doing?

299
00:19:29,680 --> 00:19:30,720
I' m fine.

300
00:19:31,160 --> 00:19:33,800
I' m just a little tired,[br]but I' m okay.

301
00:19:34,640 --> 00:19:37,030
-How's Richard doing?[br]-You don't want to know.

302
00:19:37,280 --> 00:19:39,560
No, I really, really do.

303
00:19:40,200 --> 00:19:42,480
Well, he's doing terrible!

304
00:19:44,680 --> 00:19:46,040
Really?

305
00:19:46,760 --> 00:19:48,880
Worse than when he broke up[br]with Barbara.

306
00:19:50,080 --> 00:19:53,680
-You' re not just saying that, are you?[br]-No, the man is a mess!

307
00:19:55,280 --> 00:19:57,000
Was he crying?

308
00:19:58,040 --> 00:20:01,430
Do you think he was waiting till[br]after you left, so he could cry?

309
00:20:01,640 --> 00:20:02,760
Maybe.

310
00:20:04,760 --> 00:20:05,990
I think so.

311
00:20:06,440 --> 00:20:09,440
Honey, relationships are hard.[br]Like with your mom and me.

312
00:20:09,640 --> 00:20:13,240
You know, after we graduated from[br]college, we broke up for a while.

313
00:20:13,480 --> 00:20:15,840
It seems her father,[br]your grandfather. . .

314
00:20:16,080 --> 00:20:18,600
. . .wanted her to travel around Europe[br]like he did.

315
00:20:18,800 --> 00:20:21,400
Of course, he got to do it[br]on Uncle Sam's nickel. . .

316
00:20:21,640 --> 00:20:25,760
. . .because he was also strafing[br]German troop trains at the time.

317
00:20:25,960 --> 00:20:26,760
However. . . .

318
00:21:07,640 --> 00:21:09,120
Okay, here we go.

319
00:21:09,560 --> 00:21:12,400
I am Jabba's prisoner.[br]And you. . .

320
00:21:13,200 --> 00:21:15,320
. . .have a really weird look[br]on your face.

321
00:21:15,800 --> 00:21:17,030
What? Honey, what is it?

322
00:21:17,280 --> 00:21:18,720
Did I get the hair wrong?

323
00:21:18,960 --> 00:21:22,590
Or what? Did you just[br]picture it differently? What?

324
00:21:22,800 --> 00:21:24,950
It's not you.[br]It's. . . .

325
00:21:29,680 --> 00:21:33,640
What is it? Come on, sweetie.[br]You' re, like, freaking me out here.

326
00:21:36,080 --> 00:21:38,680
I hate Chandler.[br]The bastard ruined my life!

